post_text: #pleasantvalleyproud
shared_text:
Tracy Ann
August 11 at 6:04 PM ¬∑

This right here is what sets Pleasant Valley school district apart. We will be utilizing a hybrid model this fall. We do not want the students' school supplies to go back and forth between home and school. We also do not want our parents to have to buy two sets of school supplies. So today an army of Pleasant Valley staff members came together to create 500 supply kits by grade level for each of our students to keep at home. Along with Chromebooks these kits have everything from paper and pencils, glue and scissors to white boards and markers to math manipulatives and novels. You name it these kits have it! I can not thank my staff enough for their time and dedication and to my principal Kelly Sue for leading the troops. I can't shout it loud enough #pleasantvalleyproud!

We do not want the students' school supplies to go back and forth between home and school. We also do not want our parents to have to buy two sets of school supplies. The brain buster for today is for our 7-8th grade students. - Legs in the bus
1. There are 7 girls on a bus.
2. Each girl has 7 backpacks.
3. In each backpack, there are 7 big cats.
4. For every big cat, there are 7 little cats.
How many legs are on the bus, NOT counting the driver? #pleasantvalleyproud #stayconnected

Our "brain buster" for today is for our 5-6th grade students:
Hank the hot dog vendor is trying to buy the same number of hot dogs and hot dog buns. Hot dogs are sold in packages of 6. Buns are sold in packages of 10. What's the smallest number of packages of hot dogs and of buns that Hank can buy to have a matching number of each? Leave your answer in the comments please. #pleasantvalleyproud #stayconnected

post_text: It's "Brain Buster" time! Students 6th-8th: The teacher wrote this problem on the board. "Three friends were searching for mushrooms. At the end of their search, all the mushrooms had been found by one of the three. Lucy found 2/3 of the mushrooms, Linus found 1/4 of the mushrooms, and Charlie found 1/9 of the mushrooms." Before she could sit down, Brainy Barb raised her hand. "Ms. Gorman, that is not possible." Is she right? Why or Why not? Answer below. Thanks Ms. Gorman! #pleasantvalleyproud #stayconnected

post_text: PV Middle School is excited to announce that next week, our 7th and 8th graders will be participating in #SaySomething Week. Say Something Week was started as a part of the Sandy Hook Promise. This organization was founded by several family members whose loved ones were killed at Sandy Hook Elementary School in 2012. The group was formed to unite people who value the protection of children to take meaningful actions to prevent violence.
